    <!-- Market Overview -->
    <section id="market" class="section">
      <h2>📊 Market Overview</h2>
      <p>The Montreal design market is experiencing a shift. While traditional graphic design roles remain stable, there's an emerging opportunity for designers who integrate AI tools into their workflow. Here's the current landscape as of March 2026:</p>

      <div class="stats-grid">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number">61</span>
          <span class="stat-label">"Graphiste" Jobs Found</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number">43</span>
          <span class="stat-label">English "Graphic Designer" Positions</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number">23</span>
          <span class="stat-label">"Creative Designer AI" Roles</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number">8</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Canada Job Bank Listings</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="highlight-box">
        <h3>🎯 South Shore Reality Check</h3>
        <p>The market is heavily Montreal-centric. Most positions are downtown or West Island, with very few purely South Shore opportunities. <strong>Remote-first is your best strategy.</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Olymel (Boucherville)</strong> — Active hiring for graphic designers</li>
          <li><strong>BBA Consultants (Mont-St-Hilaire)</strong> — Communications roles</li>
          <li><strong>Longueuil municipal services</strong> — Occasional openings</li>
          <li><strong>REM access</strong> — Making downtown commutes more viable</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

